---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="solar-system-size.html" headerVariant="policy">

<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-slate-800 text-white py-24">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<div class="uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-300 text-sm mb-4">
SOLAR EDUCATION CENTER
</div>

<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
What Size Solar System Do I Need?
</h1>

<p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
A complete guide to choosing the right solar system size for your home in India.
</p>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
How Solar System Size Is Calculated
</h2>

<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
The easiest way to estimate solar size is by looking at your monthly electricity bill.
Higher bills usually indicate higher electricity consumption and require larger systems.
</p>

<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">

<table class="w-full text-left">
<thead>
<tr class="border-b">
<th class="py-3">Monthly Bill</th>
<th class="py-3">Recommended System</th>
</tr>
</thead>

<tbody>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">₹500 – ₹1,500</td>
<td>1–2 kW</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">₹1,500 – ₹3,000</td>
<td>2–3 kW</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">₹3,000 – ₹5,000</td>
<td>3–5 kW</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">₹5,000 – ₹10,000</td>
<td>5–8 kW</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="py-3">₹10,000+</td>
<td>10 kW+</td>
</tr>

</tbody>
</table>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20 bg-white">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-10">
Popular Solar System Sizes
</h2>

<div class="space-y-8">

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-3xl">
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">1 kW Solar System</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Suitable for small homes with basic appliances.
Typically generates 4–5 units per day.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-3xl">
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">2 kW Solar System</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Suitable for small families.
Can power lights, fans, television and refrigerator.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-3xl">
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">3 kW Solar System</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
One of the most popular residential sizes in India.
Suitable for moderate electricity consumption.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-3xl">
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">5 kW Solar System</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Ideal for households running air conditioners and multiple appliances.
Can significantly reduce electricity bills.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-3xl">
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">10 kW Solar System</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
Designed for large homes and high-energy users.
Provides substantial long-term savings.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20">

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
Roof Space Requirements
</h2>

<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-sm">

<table class="w-full">

<thead>
<tr class="border-b">
<th class="py-3 text-left">System Size</th>
<th class="py-3 text-left">Approx Roof Area</th>
</tr>
</thead>

<tbody>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">1 kW</td>
<td>100 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">2 kW</td>
<td>200 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">3 kW</td>
<td>300 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b">
<td class="py-3">5 kW</td>
<td>500 sq ft</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="py-3">10 kW</td>
<td>1000 sq ft</td>
</tr>

</tbody>

</table>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="py-20 bg-indigo-50">

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">

<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
Not Sure Which Size Is Right?
</h2>

<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
Use our AI-powered solar calculator to receive a personalized recommendation.
</p>

<a href="index.html"
class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold">
Calculate My Solar Size
</a>

</div>

</section>
<!-- FOOTER -->

</BaseLayout>
